      • loadTutorial

        public void loadTutorial(java.lang.String filePath)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Loads the tutorial stored in the file at the specified file path. The fields store the data from the file.
        Parameters:
        filePath - the path of the file which contains the tutorial
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if the file cannot be accessed properly or is not formatted correctly

      • loadNextHint

        public void loadNextHint()
        Loads the next hint for the current sub-tutorial, i.e. the hint index is incremented. The hint index will follow 0, 1, 2, ..., n, 0, 1, 2, ...

      • loadPreviousHint

        public void loadPreviousHint()
        Loads the previous hint for the current sub-tutorial, i.e. the hint index is decremented. The hint index will follow ..., 2, 1, 0, n, n - 1, ...,

      • getStickers

        private java.awt.Color[] getStickers(java.lang.String stickerFormat)
        This returns an array of Colors containing all colours denoted in the stickerFormat parameter.
        For example, Input: "r-g" will return {Color.red, Color.green}
        Parameters:
        stickerFormat - denotes the stickers with letters separated by '-' characters.
        Returns:
        an array of Colors containing all colours denoted in the stickerFormat parameter.
